  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. This adversarial package contains broken provenance on selected ValidationResult objects: experiments were performed and results recorded, but the structured prov:wasGeneratedBy link to the generating Activity is absent for approximately half the validation results.",
